            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>The extractor is built but three memory gaps remain. First, conflict resolution — when a user corrects a fact, both old and new stick around and the agent sees contradictions. We need intelligent merging. Second, scope is too simple — user scope and conversation scope are hard walls. We need to synthesize patterns across sessions. Third and scariest: compliance. Memory is write-once, no TTL, no PII redaction. GDPR requires delete-on-request with proof. You can't sell into Europe without this.</a:t>
